This assignment requires you to create 1 file, a HTML5 document (.htm or .html).
HTML5 document

    In the body element, type your name, e-mail address, and college major.
    Place each bit of information in a paragraph element ( <p> </p> ) so that each appears on its own line.
    Place a script element Just before your closing body tag inside your HTML5 document as outlined on pages 10 & 11 of your text.
    Use your discussion board assignment resources to find out how to color all of the text in your Web page white over a black page background color. Place that code in your script element. Use the JavaScript "style" object to format your page. Hint: see "w3schools - style object (opens in a new tab or window)" below.

<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang = "en">
    <head>
        <meta charset= "utf-8">
        <title>WEB 115 Lesson 02</title>
    </head>
    <body>
        <p>Name: Kristen Nelms</p>
        <p>Email: klnelms@my.waketech.edu</p>
        <p>Major: Computer Programming & Development</p>
    <script>
        document.body.style.backgroundColor = "black";
        document.body.style.color = "white";
    </script>
    </body>
</html>
